        "created_at": "2021-04-26T16:16:05.485Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>I am new to the foundationdb (currently using V6.2.19) backups, and while creating backups in a file system, I observed we have three folders created, kvranges, snapshots, and logs. my cluster has a K-V size of 3.7G and while running the fdbbackup, I observed that the total file size of the snapshots folder was 3.7G. and if writes were happening continuously onto the cluster, the snapshot file size increased as well.</p>\n<p>Is this the expected behaviour?</p>\n<p>I was under the impression \u201cfull backup consists of an <em>inconsistent</em> copy of the data with a log of database changes that took place during the creation of that inconsistent copy\u201d, which means the mutations would be written within the logs folder.</p>\n<p>Could someone clarify how the data is stored while backing up? the explanation for RangeFileWriter( in FileBackupAgent.actor.cpp) is a bit confusing.</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance!</p>",
